1
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:06,750
Encounter

2
00:00:14,170 --> 00:00:16,370
Song Hye Kyo

3
00:00:24,550 --> 00:00:26,690
Park Bo Gum

4
00:00:33,130 --> 00:00:37,030
Boyfriend

5
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:45,130
Who that person is, and whether it is really a romance or not,

6
00:00:45,130 --> 00:00:47,810
you haven't made an official statement yet.

7
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:49,940
What kind of relationship is it exactly?

8
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:56,960
We are in a 'some' relationship.

9
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:11,080
We are in a 'some' relationship...

10
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:23,880
- Jin Hyeok! Let's clean up!
- Yes.

11
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:26,560
Run. Come on, come on.

12
00:01:29,170 --> 00:01:31,140
You've gone crazy, haven't you?

13
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:33,780
If you see it that way, there is nothing I can do about it.

14
00:01:33,780 --> 00:01:38,550
Alright. Let's say that you just went crazy momentarily. Call Chairwoman Kim immediately.

15
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:41,130
No. Let's go to Chairman Kim's house together.

16
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:43,950
Let's go there and beg for forgiveness and tell her you lost your mind for a moment.

17
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:46,710
I could only do that if I had really lost my mind.

18
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:50,370
A person in their right mind cannot live that way, as if they are not a human being.

19
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:52,040
I warned you, didn't I?

20
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:54,120
I told you to live as a useful child.

21
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,840
I have lived as a useful child until this point.

22
00:01:56,840 --> 00:02:00,650
But now, I plan to live my own life.

23
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:15,960
Episode 7

24
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,430
You haven't left yet?

25
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:27,520
I'm going to go back to Seoul after cleaning things up a bit. What a mess.

26
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,540
Our CEO is charismatic. I like it!

27
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:31,500
You can laugh?

28
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,010
When I think about what is ahead, my head hurts.

29
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:38,140
What you mean your head hurts? One person is liking another. Why does your head hurt?

30
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:42,150
It must be so nice to have your heart at ease. How are you so positive, with no plan ahead?

31
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:44,020
What about you? You don't like what's happening?

32
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:46,010
It's like cider (refreshing).

33
00:02:47,390 --> 00:02:50,290
- What about CEO?
- She's on her way. But her mom dragged her away first.

34
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:52,670
That's what I'm talking about. This is such a headache.

35
00:02:52,670 --> 00:02:55,080
I'm just saying, that woman's (Soo Hyeon's mother) whole life is a giant headache.

36
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,100
What are we going to do now? I just don't see a way out of this.

37
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,720
I'll be going back up to Seoul now.

38
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:02,310
- Bye Manager Nam and Secretary Jang.
- Bye.

39
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:03,820
- Drive safely.
- Okay.

40
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:06,600
- What are we going to do now?
- Go home and get a good night's sleep, of course.

41
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:10,710
- Will you be able to sleep?
- Yeah. I won't be able to sleep, right?

42
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:12,490
Because I'm too excited.

43
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:16,150
We are just not on the same page, are we, Ahjussi? Agh!

44
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:22,050
♫ I don't know anything except love ♫

45
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:25,990
I know it's a tiring task, but let's clean up together or later you'll be more tired.

46
00:03:25,990 --> 00:03:28,430
Yes!

47
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:30,210
Was it okay today?

48
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:33,870
Yes. I'm going to ask them to clean up.

49
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:35,040
Good job.

50
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:46,820
We are in a 'some' relationship.

51
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:22,490
Jin Hyeok

52
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:31,000
Call Jin Hyeok

53
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:43,460
- Yes, CEO.
- Where are you?

54
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:46,670
I am at the company. We are cleaning up.

55
00:04:46,670 --> 00:04:49,870
Can you meet with me for a moment? I'll come down.

56
00:04:51,370 --> 00:04:54,930
What? The whole Public Relations team is here.

57
00:04:54,930 --> 00:04:57,740
I wanted to tell everyone they did a good job and greet everyone.

58
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:59,760
So I'll come down.

59
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:16,380
You're all working so hard and so late into the night.

60
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:20,120
Today's grand opening event exceeded expectations. I want to thank all of you.

61
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:23,050
CEO, why'd you come all the way here? You must be tired.

62
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:24,410
I have some things to wrap up.

63
00:05:24,410 --> 00:05:26,280
We are also diligently wrapping things up.

64
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:29,950
What are you wrapping up? It's late. Let's go.

65
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:32,910
- It's okay to clean things up slowly.
- You said we should finish up today—

66
00:05:32,910 --> 00:05:36,350
What? When? When did she say that? Shall we all leave?

67
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,190
- Section Chief, let's go.
- Yes. Let's go.

68
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:40,880
Jin Hyeok, turn off the lights when you leave.

69
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,670
I respect you so much, CEO.

70
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,970
Good—

71
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,390
It must be fun to have so many people working together.

72
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:01,790
The CEO office is so quiet.

73
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:06,060
I don't know what I'm supposed to say.

74
00:06:06,060 --> 00:06:10,420
Why are you worried? "You were pretty cool." That should be enough.

75
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:12,450
But there were a lot of reporters.

76
00:06:12,450 --> 00:06:15,130
- CEO, from now on—
- Jin Hyeok.

77
00:06:15,130 --> 00:06:17,330
Why do you only worry about me?

78
00:06:17,330 --> 00:06:21,000
I'm used to this kind of attention, but you're not.

79
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,300
I'm worried that I might've made

80
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,620
things worse for you.

81
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:29,190
So we are each worrying about the other.

82
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:33,190
All of the things you have to deal with because of me, that was bothering me.

83
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:35,410
You see,

84
00:06:35,410 --> 00:06:38,880
I have been living with only a vague sense of who I am.

85
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:45,230
Assemblyman Cha Jong Hyeon's daughter, Taegyeong Group's divorced daughter-in-law, Donghwa Hotel's CEO ...

86
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:50,000
Today is the first day.

87
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:53,220
I'm not the Cha Soo Hyeon who was sold off to Taegyeong Group

88
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:56,220
and I'm not Cha Soo Hyeon who lives because of a hotel.

89
00:06:56,220 --> 00:07:01,480
I am also not Cha Soo Hyeon who allows the person she likes to be mistreated without reason.

90
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:04,460
Today, for the first time, my inner self feels relieved.

91
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:06,590
I feel like I threw one good punch,

92
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:10,870
so don't worry.

93
00:07:14,290 --> 00:07:17,140
Oh, I'm so hungry. I ate nothing all day.

94
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:20,150
Jin Hyeok, did you eat something?

95
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:22,540
Don't say it. Do you have squid again?

96
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,500
Once again, it's all thanks to Assistant Manager Park.

97
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:31,450
Assistant Manager Park supplied the squid last time too.

98
00:07:31,450 --> 00:07:34,190
I'm so thankful to him, each time.

99
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:38,830
At this point, it appears Assistant Manager Park is a fan of yours, and not mine.

100
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:47,230
I thought we were going to split it. Ah, so hungry.

101
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:49,250
Should I spit it out?

102
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:51,840
No, I'm joking.

103
00:08:15,910 --> 00:08:18,200
We are in a 'some' relationship.

104
00:08:24,130 --> 00:08:27,510
It's quieter than we expected, right?

105
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:30,690
I went through quite a bit, trying to block the articles.

106
00:08:30,690 --> 00:08:33,700
I'm glad. This caused me a lot of worry, as well.

107
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:37,340
The reporter. The one who asked the foolish question.

108
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:38,790
Yes?

109
00:08:39,410 --> 00:08:41,070
Yes. Yes.

110
00:08:41,070 --> 00:08:44,720
For me to find out who planted that reporter there

111
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:47,560
one night was enough.

112
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:52,180
I don't know what you mean...

113
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:57,010
Alright. Let's say that you weren't the one who planted him.

114
00:08:57,010 --> 00:08:59,620
But you still need to take care of it, right?

115
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:05,560
Get rid of Kim Jin Hyeok.

116
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:10,760
Send him to the countryside, make him stay there for a bit, and then kick him out.

117
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:14,980
If we suddenly do this, I don't think CEO Cha will just sit still.

118
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:20,160
When you planned all this, didn't you have a conclusion in mind?

119
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,750
Did you point your sword at me

120
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:25,050
with no plan whatsoever?

121
00:09:25,050 --> 00:09:28,530
Chairman! How dare I do such a thing to you—

122
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:32,090
Exactly. How dare you.

123
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:37,130
Clean it up properly.

124
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,630
Where are you going? Shall I help you?

125
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:13,420
No. I'm going to get some water.

126
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:16,770
- Me too. Let's go together. I'm thirsty.
- Assistant Manager Park, you can have a seat.

127
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,170
No need to thank me.

128
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:27,770
Just think of it as my wish for you to be happy.

129
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,650
Thank you.

130
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:32,930
It's quite disappointing, you know.

131
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:33,900
Sorry?

132
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:37,580
Between us... greeting each other so formally like this is too much, don't you think?

133
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,780
So annoying.

134
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,490
Please don't forget that the most trustworthy

135
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:46,100
sunbae in this team is me, Goo Eun Jin.

136
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,340
- Jin Hyeok.
- Yes?

137
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:53,040
This won't do. These two people will terrorize you all day today.

138
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:56,280
There are promotion gifts for the Sokcho event in our conference room.

139
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,350
Please go sort out and make a list of VIP guests who couldn't make it to the event.

140
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:01,630
We have to personally deliver them starting tomorrow.

141
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:03,520
- Will do that, Department Head.
- Let's go.

142
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,300
Why don't you sit down, Assistant Manager Park?

143
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,990
I'm really good with that kind of task, you know.

144
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:10,370
- Goo Eun Jin.
- Yes?

145
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:12,530
How about if Hye In helps Jin Hyeok?

146
00:11:12,530 --> 00:11:14,330
Yes.

147
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:21,400
Why are you so desperate?

148
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:23,550
Does love change?

149
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,770
We deliver all these in person?

150
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:32,480
Yeah. Even though you might think these promotion gifts are nothing, this is one way to manage our customers.

151
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:34,480
Like showing our sincere appreciation?

152
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:37,810
Our Public Relations Team does so many different things.

153
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:41,200
- This is the entire list, right?
- Yeah.

154
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:46,930
CEO was very cool.

155
00:11:49,590 --> 00:11:51,230
I was really surprised, too.

156
00:11:51,230 --> 00:11:53,680
No, your heart must have fluttered.

157
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:01,670
By the way, something makes me worried.

158
00:12:02,570 --> 00:12:04,030
Like what?

159
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:07,110
I've met this strange person recently.

160
00:12:07,110 --> 00:12:10,670
This man... I don't know how he got my number, but he called and

161
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:15,710
- asked me to meet him, saying it was about you, Kim Jin Hyeok.
- Me?

162
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:20,130
Someone uploaded on our anonymous forum a slanderous post about CEO not long ago, remember?

163
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:25,020
He told me to write one, saying that would get me promoted.

164
00:12:26,690 --> 00:12:29,060
But it wasn't me who wrote that.

165
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:35,300
It's strange, isn't it? He already knew that

166
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:38,330
you were the one with CEO in the news article.

167
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:41,370
Who can it be? Why?

168
00:12:41,370 --> 00:12:43,560
It's so obvious! It must be Taegyeong.

169
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:47,010
That's why I said I'm worried for you. You might be having hard times like this.

170
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:51,440
Keep your guard up and watch out. They are scary people.

171
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:55,960
But Hye In... Why did they ask you to write that?

172
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,790
You are my friend after all.

173
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:02,260
I must have looked like I had a lot to complain about this company.

174
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:12,500
Cuba's Future Hospitality and Tourism Business Obstacles

175
00:13:15,780 --> 00:13:18,080
Your evening appointment got canceled, CEO.

176
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:21,630
It seems like the leader has a meeting with the orchestra.

177
00:13:22,580 --> 00:13:24,340
Reschedule it for another day, then.

178
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:25,780
Yes, ma'am.

179
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:38,640
Should we have dinner together?

180
00:13:53,190 --> 00:13:55,330
Should we have dinner together?

181
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,900
Kim Jin Hyeok.

182
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,080
May I ask who you are?

183
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,270
I'm CEO Jeong Woo Seok's secretary.

184
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:33,340
Could you spare us some time?

185
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:37,010
Please set up an appointment for later. I already have plans.

186
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:38,900
It won't take long.

187
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:41,260
It's not as if we are in a 'some' relationship or anything.

188
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:48,410
I wanted to... confirm something.

189
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:51,190
Please go ahead.

190
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:56,070
Well... I mean that Sokcho "happening."

191
00:14:56,070 --> 00:14:57,870
Is that for real?

192
00:14:59,450 --> 00:15:02,470
When one person has taken a chance to sincerely express feelings,

193
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:05,030
I can't call it a "happening."

194
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:09,060
So you are saying that it is true.

195
00:15:10,390 --> 00:15:12,390
Have you confirmed everything then?

196
00:15:14,060 --> 00:15:16,080
Somewhat.

197
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,800
I also have something to confirm.

198
00:15:21,070 --> 00:15:25,920
What could be the reason you wanted to confirm that?

199
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,480
The reason?

200
00:15:31,850 --> 00:15:34,440
Out of an oppa's* heart.
("oppa" means older brother but is also used for one's boyfriend)

201
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:40,820
Well, then... It's freezing.

202
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:05,900
Out of an oppa's heart. This is similar to love, isn't it?

203
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:11,320
That's... what I'd think. Yes.

204
00:16:16,260 --> 00:16:19,520
What's the point of caring for my skin?

205
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,690
There is no one who will see or care.

206
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:24,750
And someone is on a date.

207
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,900
New chat request has arrived.

208
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,020
Member Lee Dae Chan has sent you a chat request.

209
00:16:35,330 --> 00:16:38,840
Why don't we meet in person?

210
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:42,600
Oh my!

211
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:47,030
If I get rejected, let's just delete this account.

212
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:50,430
Ah, seriously. Wait a little bit.

213
00:16:50,430 --> 00:16:52,840
I'm busy but I will make some time.

214
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,860
It's here, here, here.

215
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:59,140
I told you! You have to wait and be patient!

216
00:16:59,140 --> 00:17:02,690
How can this thing make me so nervous? Should I workout in the meantime?

217
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:04,620
No, why don't you shave first?

218
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:07,730
- Beverages on the house.
- On the house?

219
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,340
Your colleagues must be giving you a hard time, right?

220
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:15,970
I'm constantly getting looks of jealousy.

221
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:18,470
The back of my head tingles.

222
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:20,820
It's quieter than I expected.

223
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:23,550
I thought it would be on the news and everything, making some serious noise.

224
00:17:23,550 --> 00:17:26,150
It appears that someone who's not happy with all this might have blocked all the articles.

225
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:29,060
What a shame. The headline could have been awesome.

226
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:32,540
"CEO Cha and her 'some.'"

227
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:37,560
I'm not even a celebrity, but I am making so much of a fuss with my 'some' relationship.

228
00:17:41,930 --> 00:17:45,580
Since you have brought it up, CEO ...

229
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:50,120
I'm going to stop being in a 'some' relationship with you.

230
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,890
Are you saying that we should end things now?

231
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:56,480
Yes.

232
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:08,150
- How can you, I mean—
- I am certain now.

233
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:13,160
When your doubt recedes, and your feelings of liking become more certain

234
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:18,050
that's when you should end the 'some' relationship.

235
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:25,510
You can quit. I will continue to be in the 'some' relationship.

236
00:18:25,510 --> 00:18:27,660
What do you mean? We should start (a new relationship) together.

237
00:18:27,660 --> 00:18:30,070
You were the one who made a joke first.

238
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:33,170
I will stop joking around now.

239
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:38,300
Then, from now, why don't we sincerely think about our future?

240
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:41,320
What should we do for fun?

241
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:44,300
Is there anything you want to do?

242
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:46,770
Food tour around Mangwon-dong.

243
00:18:46,770 --> 00:18:49,750
Secretary Jang would always brag about that. She never takes me with her though.

244
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:53,260
Deal! Let's go together. Right...

245
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:57,830
Can you skate? It's winter. Should we go skating sometime?

246
00:18:57,830 --> 00:19:00,790
