493
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:06,990
Everyone went out of their way to take time out for this, so you should eat.

494
00:38:06,990 --> 00:38:09,440
Because of that ridiculous talk of joining parties,

495
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:12,000
it seems as if I might have to fast.

496
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,190
Eat? Hah!

497
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:18,250
Cha Soo Hyeon. The daughter who is losing you votes, Assemblyman Cha Jong Hyeon.

498
00:38:18,250 --> 00:38:22,910
Don't you need those votes back, even if it's by merging with the Hwamin Party?

499
00:38:22,910 --> 00:38:26,200
Currently, not a single person can predict

500
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:28,080
whether I'll lose

501
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:32,500
or win more votes because of my daughter's situation.

502
00:38:37,590 --> 00:38:42,110
Haven't we made things worse with each other right now?

503
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:45,220
The raw fish is good today.

504
00:38:45,220 --> 00:38:47,930
Dine with your heart at ease.

505
00:38:51,690 --> 00:38:53,400
Was this meeting planned?

506
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,590
What did you talk about with Assemblyman Kim?

507
00:38:55,590 --> 00:38:58,010
CEO Kim of the Hwamin party went in before you.

508
00:38:58,010 --> 00:39:00,640
Was it an opportunity for you to talk about merging parties?

509
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:06,370
It was an opportunity to confirm that we do not want to merge parties.

510
00:39:06,370 --> 00:39:07,060
Well, then.

511
00:39:07,060 --> 00:39:08,860
Assemblyman, a word, please!

512
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:11,580
A word, please!

513
00:39:11,580 --> 00:39:13,730
Assemblyman!

514
00:39:24,790 --> 00:39:28,640
Where do you think the order came from?

515
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:33,390
Is it that the staff training is terrible, or are you being rude because you have the CEO's support?

516
00:39:33,390 --> 00:39:38,680
We barely stopped further hassles by transferring you to Sokcho, so let's behave well. Alright?

517
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:45,260
It's a hotel that I received as my divorce settlement, but it was everything to me.

518
00:39:53,940 --> 00:39:59,770
I have been living with only a vague sense of who I am.

519
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:16,260
Today is day one.

520
00:40:16,260 --> 00:40:19,470
I'm going to stop being in a 'some' relationship with you.

521
00:40:19,470 --> 00:40:21,000
Are you saying that we should end things?

522
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,250
I am certain now.

523
00:40:23,250 --> 00:40:27,110
When your doubt recedes, and your feelings of liking become more certain,

524
00:40:27,110 --> 00:40:29,580
that's when you should end the 'some' relationship.

525
00:40:58,830 --> 00:41:01,010
Give it to me.

526
00:41:01,010 --> 00:41:03,700
Happy birthday to you.

527
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,320
I really miss her.

528
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:20,820
How could I not have a single photo of her in my phone?

529
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:32,470
32 Hannam 3rd street Cheongdam-dong

530
00:41:36,910 --> 00:41:39,270
One hour and forty minutes

531
00:41:39,270 --> 00:41:41,200
It's close.

532
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:19,050
Jin Hyeok?

533
00:42:23,830 --> 00:42:27,060
You're much closer to my neighborhood than I thought.

534
00:42:27,060 --> 00:42:30,360
It's a perfect distance for running.

535
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:34,260
Then I guess I'll have to run that distance some time too.

536
00:42:34,260 --> 00:42:37,970
No, no. It might be a bit far for you.

537
00:42:43,730 --> 00:42:47,790
Since you've made it this far, would you like some water or something?

538
00:42:47,790 --> 00:42:50,250
No, I'm not thirsty at all.

539
00:42:58,260 --> 00:43:01,290
I don't know if I would call that not being thirsty.

540
00:43:02,210 --> 00:43:03,660
The water tastes good.

541
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:06,600
- Should I give you another bottle?
- No, it's enough.

542
00:43:07,090 --> 00:43:09,300
Wait here for a bit.

543
00:44:04,580 --> 00:44:06,940
Looks like there is no more.

544
00:44:06,940 --> 00:44:09,640
You're flustered because I came suddenly, right?

545
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:15,010
It's not that. It's... because it's the first time.

546
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:21,790
It's the first time anyone has visited me at my home, so I don't know what to do.

547
00:44:23,470 --> 00:44:28,140
Secretary Jang visits me sometimes, but she just leaves on her own, so...

548
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:32,040
Don't worry, I'll leave on my own, when the time is right.

549
00:44:34,620 --> 00:44:37,290
I think this is nicer than a model home.

550
00:44:37,290 --> 00:44:40,280
I've never been inside such a great home.

551
00:44:40,280 --> 00:44:44,420
It may be large, but there is no warmth.

552
00:44:45,740 --> 00:44:49,910
Don't you get bored, living in such a large house alone?

553
00:44:49,910 --> 00:44:54,540
Who knows? Time passes when I am working.

554
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:02,800
So tell me now.

555
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:07,790
It's such a cold day, so how did you come to run all the way here?

556
00:45:16,210 --> 00:45:19,960
At first, I was planning only to run to the Han River.

557
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:26,030
Seeing the Han River made me think of you, CEO.

558
00:45:26,030 --> 00:45:31,520
So I looked through my phone and realized that I don't have a single photo of you in there.

559
00:45:32,490 --> 00:45:35,820
I thought that if I ran towards you,

560
00:45:35,820 --> 00:45:39,360
then I'll be too tired and my feelings of missing you will disappear.

561
00:45:40,310 --> 00:45:42,200
So I ran some more.

562
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:44,650
I was tired to death,

563
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:48,330
but then I missed you even more.

564
00:45:50,310 --> 00:45:54,320
But then maybe you felt pity for me, because just at that exact time, you appeared.

565
00:45:54,320 --> 00:45:56,750
It's daebak, isn't it?

566
00:45:56,750 --> 00:45:59,500
You always run towards me, Jin Hyeok.

567
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:03,170
To Sokcho and to my house.

568
00:46:04,730 --> 00:46:07,040
Am I like a stalker?

569
00:46:08,150 --> 00:46:11,110
Let's say that you are like a boyfriend.

570
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:20,380
Boyfriend.

571
00:46:27,320 --> 00:46:29,710
Suddenly it feels like spring.

572
00:46:36,020 --> 00:46:39,590
So, let's take a photo, you and me.

573
00:46:39,590 --> 00:46:40,480
Here?

574
00:46:40,480 --> 00:46:43,420
Yes. I told you, I ran all the way here because I didn't have a photo of you.

575
00:46:43,420 --> 00:46:44,440
Let me look at the mirror, first...

576
00:46:44,440 --> 00:46:46,180
You don't need to, you look pretty.

577
00:46:46,180 --> 00:46:47,410
This is so sudden...

578
00:46:47,410 --> 00:46:51,830
Here we go. One, two, three!

579
00:46:53,530 --> 00:46:55,180
One more time.

580
00:46:55,180 --> 00:46:58,060
One, two, three!

581
00:46:58,060 --> 00:46:59,110
You're taking so many.

582
00:46:59,110 --> 00:47:03,030
I want to have a lot. One, two, three!

583
00:47:08,020 --> 00:47:12,760
♫ in my eyes, as I look at you ♫

584
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:16,050
♫ when love is reflected in them ♫

585
00:47:16,050 --> 00:47:19,850
♫ like the falling stars ♫

586
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:25,100
♫ those beautiful moments  ♫

587
00:47:25,160 --> 00:47:27,050
You always run towards me, Jin Hyeok.

588
00:47:27,050 --> 00:47:31,660
To Sokcho and to my home.

589
00:47:31,660 --> 00:47:35,630
♫ it becomes engraved in my heart ♫

590
00:47:35,630 --> 00:47:39,210
♫ it becomes stained ♫

591
00:47:39,210 --> 00:47:43,720
♫ I know I belong to you ♫

592
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:45,750
Do they call this a mismatch?

593
00:47:45,750 --> 00:47:49,020
No.

594
00:47:49,020 --> 00:47:50,950
It's a collaboration.

595
00:47:50,950 --> 00:47:52,920
Collaboration...

596
00:47:52,920 --> 00:47:54,870
♫ I hope that this is forever ♫

597
00:47:54,870 --> 00:47:59,280
♫ now I belong ♫

598
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:03,420
♫ to you ♫

599
00:48:03,420 --> 00:48:06,180
♫ my feeling grows deeper and deeper ♫

600
00:48:06,180 --> 00:48:08,180
Let's say that you are like a boyfriend.

601
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:11,460
Boyfriend.

602
00:48:12,520 --> 00:48:15,140
Suddenly it feels like spring.

603
00:48:16,990 --> 00:48:20,530
♫ that I am by your side ♫

604
00:48:20,530 --> 00:48:23,750
♫ so that you can believe that ♫

605
00:48:23,750 --> 00:48:26,510
♫ I want to do that ♫

606
00:48:26,510 --> 00:48:28,850
♫ I know ♫

607
00:48:28,850 --> 00:48:32,150
Donghwa Hotel, End-of-Year Party, Masquerade
Concept

608
00:49:03,870 --> 00:49:07,080
You have class with Chef Jang today, don't you?

609
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:08,530
Yes.

610
00:49:08,530 --> 00:49:14,510
Visit Teacher Kim's shop and change into the outfit I prepared for you before you go.

611
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:17,120
The article came out,

612
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:22,810
so everyone else taking the class will be looking forward to seeing your face.

613
00:49:23,440 --> 00:49:28,800
Your husband is having an affair, so they will want to see what you look like.

614
00:49:29,430 --> 00:49:34,060
At times like this, you must not look untidy, ever. Smile even more,

615
00:49:34,060 --> 00:49:36,620
but only just so, lest you look silly.

616
00:49:38,760 --> 00:49:40,420
Yes.

617
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:53,430
So many eyes are on you.

618
00:49:53,430 --> 00:49:57,550
How about going to work on time, especially on days like today?

619
00:49:57,550 --> 00:50:02,040
Soo Hyeon, let's get divorced.

620
00:50:04,830 --> 00:50:06,820
Please grant my request.

621
00:50:41,690 --> 00:50:44,490
It's not even my birthday. Why?

622
00:50:44,490 --> 00:50:47,880
I think we should stop having uncomfortable meetings like this.

623
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:52,350
I am grateful for what you have done up to now.

624
00:50:55,060 --> 00:50:58,260
Let's say the reason that we broke up is a difference in personalities.

625
00:50:59,870 --> 00:51:01,380
Yes.

626
00:51:07,900 --> 00:51:11,360
I feel I will always remember today, whenever I see them.

627
00:51:12,320 --> 00:51:14,570
This is a farewell, after all.

628
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:32,000
- Enjoy your meal.
- Yes.

629
00:51:34,150 --> 00:51:38,390
Only one bottle each today. I'm not used to drinking in the afternoon.

630
00:51:38,390 --> 00:51:41,860
With the articles about the merger of political parties, you must be seething. You're having a drink during the day.

631
00:51:41,860 --> 00:51:44,580
Why become upset at such a ridiculous article?

632
00:51:44,580 --> 00:51:46,180
I have to see you.

633
00:51:46,180 --> 00:51:50,520
Then shall you and I sit in a café, with earphones on our ears?

634
00:51:50,520 --> 00:51:53,350
Yes, it is weird for men to have coffee together, isn't it?

635
00:51:53,350 --> 00:51:54,830
Seon Joo, welcome.

636
00:51:54,830 --> 00:51:57,980
Why would you summon me on a weekend afternoon?

637
00:51:57,980 --> 00:52:01,020
It's been a long time.

638
00:52:01,020 --> 00:52:04,460
The TV screen works magic. Ahjussi, you look aged in real life.

639
00:52:04,460 --> 00:52:06,160
She is as rude as ever, please understand.

640
00:52:06,160 --> 00:52:08,250
We are all getting older together, so must I put on airs?

641
00:52:08,250 --> 00:52:11,190
If you say you are getting old like me, you are the one who's losing out.

642
00:52:11,190 --> 00:52:13,240
So what is on the agenda for this meeting?

643
00:52:13,240 --> 00:52:16,050
Has the news already spread that I signed my divorce papers?

644
00:52:16,050 --> 00:52:18,230
What is she talking about?

645
00:52:20,530 --> 00:52:23,650
Both of you should be relieved of your duties now.

646
00:52:23,650 --> 00:52:25,650
What did my brother say when he left us?

647
00:52:25,650 --> 00:52:29,700
He even wrote on his suicide note, "Please take care of my young Seon Joo."

648
00:52:29,700 --> 00:52:33,760
You guys have no conscience. You don't take care of me.

649
00:52:37,190 --> 00:52:40,290
I don't think one bottle each will be enough today.

650
00:52:43,110 --> 00:52:46,530
Assemblyman, will the two parties really merge?

651
00:52:46,530 --> 00:52:50,190
My oppa is about to have afternoon drinks in heaven.

652
00:52:50,190 --> 00:52:52,390
What do you know about politics? Let's talk about something else.

653
00:52:52,390 --> 00:52:56,960
What don't I know? Honestly, if my oppa hadn't used a gun to leave us early,

654
00:52:56,960 --> 00:53:00,800
Ahjussi, you wouldn't have gone on strike denouncing the suppression of the media.

655
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,520
Why are you bringing that up now?

656
00:53:02,520 --> 00:53:04,360
No, she is right.

657
00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:08,750
That was how I became the "citizen's anchorman," and how I was recruited into political circles.

658
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:10,690
Everything she is saying is correct. So what's wrong?

659
00:53:10,690 --> 00:53:11,900
Oppa, you are the bigger coward.

660
00:53:11,900 --> 00:53:14,550
Ahjussi at least fought in my oppa's place.

661
00:53:14,550 --> 00:53:19,590
Manager Nam, I mean, Nam Young Shik, you gave up on being a journalist and disappeared.

662
00:53:19,590 --> 00:53:21,390
Ah, seriously! Give me that bottle.

663
00:53:21,390 --> 00:53:24,220
You can have soda.

664
00:53:24,220 --> 00:53:27,620
She says we're getting old together. Pour her one.

665
00:53:28,860 --> 00:53:31,870
Ahjussi, you sure know how to hold a grudge.

666
00:53:45,130 --> 00:53:51,970
Jang Soo Fruits

667
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:54,020
It's so cold, why did you come?

668
00:53:54,020 --> 00:53:57,130
Because it's cold, I wanted you to finish sooner and go home.

669
00:53:57,130 --> 00:53:59,150
Did you take your cold medicine?

670
00:53:59,150 --> 00:54:02,760
I got a shot, and I get better right away.

671
00:54:02,760 --> 00:54:04,690
That is a relief.

672
00:54:07,490 --> 00:54:09,590
How is work?

673
00:54:10,250 --> 00:54:11,920
I'm having fun.

674
00:54:11,920 --> 00:54:14,910
Your face doesn't look like you're having fun.

675
00:54:20,430 --> 00:54:24,730
Dad, a novelist that I like wrote

676
00:54:26,090 --> 00:54:29,800
that to love someone, you must make an effort.

677
00:54:31,770 --> 00:54:34,540
That's... very hard.

678
00:54:37,620 --> 00:54:41,910
That is what the word "effort" means. You are not finished.

679
00:54:41,910 --> 00:54:43,390
It's saying to exert yourself.

680
00:54:43,390 --> 00:54:45,450
It is hard.

681
00:54:46,300 --> 00:54:50,200
So is our son starting to love someone?

682
00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:54,950
I guess so?

683
00:54:57,660 --> 00:55:01,630
I'm always sorry that Mom and Dad haven't been able to help you very much,

684
00:55:01,630 --> 00:55:06,170
and you've had to work so hard.

685
00:55:06,170 --> 00:55:10,830
What do you mean? I think of myself as a "gold spoon."*
(*born into privilege)

686
00:55:10,830 --> 00:55:15,630
You're a learned man. Do you not know the difference between "dirt spoon" and "gold spoon?" How are you a "gold spoon"?

687
00:55:15,630 --> 00:55:22,400
Dad. There were a lot of kids who took out loans to go to college because they couldn't pay their tuition.

688
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:25,380
Those guys are still paying off their debt.

689
00:55:25,380 --> 00:55:29,330
You paid for my tuition during all of my years at college,

690
00:55:29,330 --> 00:55:35,280
you fed me, and you let me sleep under a roof. That's being privileged to me.

691
00:55:37,610 --> 00:55:42,780
If there's one thing your mom and I did well, it's giving birth to an amazing son.

692
00:55:49,190 --> 00:55:51,480
Hey, Dad.

693
00:55:52,920 --> 00:55:55,930
I've been transferred to Sokcho.

694
00:55:55,930 --> 00:55:59,760
Sokcho? Why so far away?

695
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:00,900
They said the public relations team is like that.

696
00:56:00,900 --> 00:56:04,520
It's a field that has to know about all their locations, so there's a lot of moving.

697
00:56:04,520 --> 00:56:09,540
Even so... it's just after you entered the company. Mom will be shocked.

698
00:56:09,540 --> 00:56:11,940
That's why I'm telling you beforehand.

699
00:56:11,940 --> 00:56:15,290
Help Mom out, alright?

700
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:25,740
Let's go. Let's go help her.

701
00:56:31,690 --> 00:56:33,690
You're surprised, right?

702
00:56:34,490 --> 00:56:36,180
It's a joke, right? Honey?

703
00:56:36,180 --> 00:56:39,680
Why would we joke about something like this? It's not even funny.

704
00:56:39,680 --> 00:56:43,920
But why? It hasn't been that long since you started working at the company.

705
00:56:43,920 --> 00:56:49,030
The hotel at Sokcho is really starting to do well, but I guess they don't have enough workers.

706
00:56:49,030 --> 00:56:51,400
So that's why they've selected the new workers to move there.

707
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:54,700
It's a handful of people, chosen from all across the nation.

708
00:56:54,700 --> 00:56:58,540
Did you do something wrong?

709
00:56:58,540 --> 00:56:59,310
What?

710
00:56:59,310 --> 00:57:00,820
Stop talking nonsense.

711
00:57:00,820 --> 00:57:03,280
It's because it's a little strange.

712
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:06,290
That thing. What is it? A pair of woman's shoes in your room.

713
00:57:06,290 --> 00:57:07,980
Woman's shoes?

714
00:57:07,980 --> 00:57:12,530
I thought it was a gift for me so I tried them on, but they didn't fit.

715
00:57:12,530 --> 00:57:19,360
Are you, perhaps, saying that you got moved to a different location and planning on starting a shoe business?

716
00:57:20,500 --> 00:57:25,310
My mother's imagination is quite something else. Why would I start a business?

717
00:57:25,310 --> 00:57:28,830
He can only sell fruit kind of well; what business—

718
00:57:28,830 --> 00:57:29,940
What are the woman's shoes in your room?

719
00:57:29,940 --> 00:57:33,760
Huh? Oh, the thing is...

720
00:57:35,030 --> 00:57:41,040
It's something from Cuba. I just kept them to use as props for shooting later.

721
00:57:41,040 --> 00:57:42,990
Really?

722
00:57:44,330 --> 00:57:47,050
I thought of every possible scenario.

723
00:57:47,050 --> 00:57:52,010
I'm going to Sokcho Hotel to help out for just a bit. Don't think of anything else, Mom.

724
00:57:52,010 --> 00:57:54,980
But still, it's so far.

725
00:57:54,980 --> 00:58:00,210
Does that area have something with you? You even served the military in Gangwon-do.

726
00:58:00,210 --> 00:58:02,460
Huh, I guess so. There is some sort of fated connection.

727
00:58:02,460 --> 00:58:04,150
Nonsense.

728
00:58:08,970 --> 00:58:10,250
What's wrong with you today, Honey?

729
00:58:10,250 --> 00:58:11,560
What? Why?

730
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:13,420
What? It's because I'm hungry.

731
00:58:13,420 --> 00:58:15,720
Are you hungry?

732
00:58:15,720 --> 00:58:17,060
Is it already this late?

